headline: Lucas Oil Launches New Hybrid Product Line, Additives Purpose-Built for All Hybrid Engines
summary: Lucas Oil, the nation's top-selling brand in oil additives and performance lubricants, today announced the launch of its first-ever product line designed exclusively for hybrid vehicles: Hybrid Oil Treatment and Hybrid Fuel Treatment with HybridShield Technology. The products will be on display at the 2025 AAPEX Show in the Lucas Oil Product booth number A1634 and featured in the AAPEX New Product Showcase.

headline: CARFAX: Highest Used Car Prices In 18 Months - Some Older Models Close in Price To New Models
summary: New data from CARFAX shows that average Used Car Prices have climbed to their highest point in 18 months to just under $25,000. That means car shoppers around this time are paying around $1,300 more for the average used vehicle than they would have just a year and a half ago.

headline: A Fresh Look at Ford (F) Valuation as Shares Gain Momentum
summary: Ford Motor (F) has been moving quietly in recent trading sessions, drawing renewed interest from investors looking at its recent returns. With shares up 3% over the past month and 18% over the past 3 months, Ford’s performance has started catching attention. See our latest analysis for Ford Motor. headline: 1 S&P 500 Stock to Target This Week and 2 We Ignore
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is home to the biggest and most well-known companies in the market, making it a go-to index for investors seeking stability. But not all large-cap stocks are created equal - some are struggling with slowing growth, declining margins, or increased competition.
